Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Valequez Livingston not in court, in custody.  Attorney Imran Kurter in court for Valequez Livingston.  Attorney William T Berens for Megan Marie Newport in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Case in court for status conference. Defense counsel requested adjournment to allow more time for expert doctor. Status conference scheduled for November 18, 2022 at 10:00 am.

Defendant Valequez Livingston in court with attorney Imran Kurter.  Chad Wozniak appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Case in court for return on doctors report.  State does not dispute the findings, however the defense contests the report. Parties have off record discussion. On record. Defense to provide private dr. report to provide to state. Court sets status date in Branch 4.  Status conference scheduled for October 10, 2022 at 09:00 am.
Order for Examination under 971.16, Wis. Stats. (Not Guilty by Reason of Mental Disease or Defect)

Attorney Imran Kurter in court, defendant Valequez Livingston not in court, in custody.  Chad Wozniak appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Case in court for scheduling hearing, however defense requests NGI evaluation.  Order for Examination, signed and filed.   NGI evaluation. Case remains calendared in Branch 4.  Doctor's Report Return scheduled for August 19, 2022 at 10:00 am.

Attorney Imran Kurter in court, defendant Valequez Livingston not in court, in custody.  John J Rejowski appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Case in court for Bail/Bond Hearing. Officer Darryl Anderson makes statement to the court. Bail motion by defense argued and denied by the Court. Court orders $200,000 bond and conditions remain unchanged. Defense counsel received discovery today.   Defense requests more time to review case. Case remains calendared in Branch 4. Scheduling Conference is 7/19/22 at 10:00 am.

Defendant Valequez Livingston in court, appear by video with attorney Imran Kurter, appear by video.  Defendant Valequez Livingston in custody.  Megan Newport appeared in person for the State of Wisconsin.  
Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the State: Detective M. Fedel.    State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty.  Case is adjourned to Branch 46.  Due to assignment of Assistant District Attorney, the defendant is advised that case is reassigned to Judge Hanrahan Br 04. Defense wants to be heard on bail. Date provided by Br. 04 Clerk.  Bail/bond hearing scheduled for June 29, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Defense Motion to Reduce Bail for Defendant; received, filed, and forwarded to the Judge for review.

Attorney Imran Kurter appear a friend of the court in court, appear in person. Defendant Valequez Livingston not in court, in custody.  Abby Rockendorf appeared in person for the State of Wisconsin.  
Case set for a preliminary hearing. State witness present. Attorney Kurter needs more time to be appointed. Court ordered case adjourned for CAUSE for a Preliminary Hearing in Preliminary Hearing Court, Room 146 of the Criminal Justice Facility.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for June 22, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Valequez Livingston not in court, defendant in custody.  Ian Vance-Curzan appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Case set for a preliminary hearing. States witness is on standby. SPD has not appointed counsel. Court ordered case adjourned for CAUSE for a Preliminary Hearing in Preliminary Hearing Court, Room 146 of the Criminal Justice Facility.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for May 24, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 5.  Court ordered no possession or use of controlled substances without a valid prescription.  No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Valequez Livingston in court with attorney Dawn Marie Rablin.  Defendant Valequez Livingston in custody.  Jessica Ann Behling appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Valequez Livingston appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Feiss, Branch 46. Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold the defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.  Commissioner advised DNA sample has NOT been obtained from the Defendant.  Court ordered the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department to obtain DNA sample from the Defendant.  Court advised Defendant he may qualify to have the DNA sample data expunged if he meets the conditions under Wisconsin Statutes Section 165.77(4).  
This hearing will be streamed live on Dacast:  https://iframe.dacast.com/live/4dafbf46-ed15-c11c-fa22-a58262833632/99073afd-37c2-acfa-830d-b1ddcaebf0ea  Preliminary hearing scheduled for April 26, 2022 at 08:30 am.
